Before Mango season is over, try this easy peasy mango mug cake.Kids will absolutely love it along with you. Instead of having store bought cake, try this at home. 

Recipe-
In a big mug add 3 tbsp milk(approx 1/4 cup), 1/4 cup sweet mango pulp, 2 tbsp oil, 1/2 tsp vanilla essence(optional), 2-3 tbsp jaggery (adjust sweetness as per taste), 1/4 cup wheat flour, 1/2 tsp baking soda and 1/2 tsp baking powder. Mix well. Top it up with some walnuts (optional)

Microwave it for 75-90 secs and then top it up with mango pulp or cream, add dark chocolate chips and serve.

Lunch in 10 mins. If you’re a vegetarian like me and trying to meet your protein requirements, this is for you. Simple, easy and healthy meal for a summer afternoon. 

Recipe-
1. Dry roast 1 bowl Makhan and keep it aside.
2. In a pan add 1 tsp oil, 1 green chili, 4-5 chopped garlic pods , mustard seeds and jeera. Once it’s starts to crackle, add 1 tsp ginger, handful of curry leaves and 1 chopped onion.
2. Cook untill onions are translucent. Add 1 cup sprouts, add little water, cover and cook until sprouts are soft or use steamed or boiled sprouts.
3. Add 1 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chili powder and salt to taste. Mix well.
4. Switch of the flame and then add 2 cup whisked curd along with roasted makhanas. 
5. Garnish it with coriander leaves and serve it with hot rice or chapatis.

Easy, tasty and healthy breakfast in mins. Instead of Daal Paratha make this Daal Utappam from the leftover daal.

Recipe-
1. Blend 1 cup cooked daal, 1 cup besan, 4-5 garlic pods, 1 tsp ginger, salt to taste, 1 tsp turmeric, 1 green chili, 1 tsp jeera  with 3-4 sip water. You can add more water if daal is thick.
2. Pour batter over heated pan, top it up with veggies of choice. Cook from both sides and serve with chutney.

Blender Sooji Chocolate Banana Bread. The most easiest, simplest and tastiest banana bread recipe you can ever get! Homemade breads and cakes are the best to enjoy it guiltfree!

Recipe-
1. In a blender jar add 1 banana, 1 cup suji, 1 cup jaggery, 1/2 cup cocoa powder, 1/2 cup curd, 1/2 cup milk, 1/4 cup oil and blend it to a smooth mixture.
2. Add 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp baking powder and 1/2 tsp vinegar. Mix well and transfer it to a greased lined baking dish. Top it up with chocolate chips and walnuts.
3. Bake it at 180degrees for 30-35 mins in a preheated oven.
4. Cool it down completely before slicing.

You can make this in airfryer or even on stove the way you make cakes!

Healthiest Cold Chocolate you can sip through your summer time! This has goodness of antioxidants, omega 3 and rich in fibre! Perfect way to sip cold chocolate and keep yourself hydrated!

Recipe-
Blend together 2 spoon of soaked chia seeds, 3-4 pieces of dark chocolate(you add more of chocolate and can also use normal chocolate), 1 spoon unsweetened cocoa powder 1 glass water and 5-6 deseeded soft dates( of dates are hard, soak them in water for 30 mins and can replace dates with jaggery).
 Serves chilled with ice!

Each paratha has approx 20gm Protein. So nutritious, healthy, tasty and keeps you full for good time. Great way to add sprouts to your diet. You can have this for any meal of the day. 

Recipe-
1. Coarsely grind 2 cups of sprouts and add it in a bowl.
2. Now add 1 chopped onion, handful coriander leaves, 1+ 1/2 cups besan, 1 tsp grated ginger, 1 finely chopped green chili, 4-5 finely chopped garlic pods, salt to taste, 1 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp chaat masala and 1 tsp jeera powder. Mix and make soft dough. Add water only if required.
3. Divide it into balls, roll flat using hand, water and parchment paper. 
4. Slow cook on low flame on both sides and then apply ghee and serve hot with chutney and curd.
